name: CatalogueItemConfirmation
definition:
This refers to electronic communication from the Data Recipient to the Data Source indicating what action has been taken on the item. The confirmation process occurs in the recipient’s data pool. Confirmation is not mandatory. When used, it provides for the following outcomes: 
1. Synchronised: data is integrated, in synch and added to the synchronisation list. 
2. Accepted: data is added to the synchronisation list and will be in synch. 
3. Rejected: data will no longer be synchronised or updates will no longer be provided. 
4. Review: a request to the data source to “review” their data because the data recipient has received discrepant data which they cannot synchronise. If the data was previously synchronised, it will be removed from the synchronisation list.

definition: A description of any species of animal that was used for determining LC and LD other than the norm.

name: OrganicClaim
definition: Any claim to indicate the organic status of a trade item or of one or more of its components.

extensions.definition: A certification in relation to an organic claim.

name: SkinProductInformation
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different types of skin the product is intended for.

name: ApplicablePaymentTerms
definition: Payment terms and conditions by which a payment can be made for a trade item.

name: ChemicalIngredientPropertyInformation
definition: Information on any chemical properties a chemical may have according to a specific regulation for example carcinogen.

extensions.definition: Chemical property information for a regulated chemical.

name: TargetMarketDiscountRestrictions
definition: Determines whether an item requires a license or permit to sell within a specific target market.

extensions.name: discountRestrictionTargetMarketCountry
extensions.definition: The target market that any restrictions on a discount applies to.

name: ClinicalStorageHandlingTypeCode
definition: The type of Clinical Storage Handling of the medical device.

name: RouteOfExposureCode
definition: The means by which  living organisms can come into contact with a hazardous substance for example  dermal, Inhalation, ingestion.

name: AuthorisationResponse
definition: Not available.

extensions.definition: Not available.
Not available.

name: WorkingPressureRatingClassCode
definition: The state of the medium being pushed through the pipe for example water or steam in relation to determining working pressure.

name: HealthcareGroupedProductCode
definition: A code representing whether a healthcare item is considered by the manufacturer to be more than a single item or for example: kit or combination for FDA 21CFR 830.

name: LethalDoseConcentrationInformation
definition: Details on any lethal dose or concentration of a chemical in a trade item.

name: ComponentInformation
definition: A constituent part of a trade item that is packaged separately.

name: ONIXElectronicPublicationInformation
definition: Describes a usage constraint on a digital product, whether imposed by DRM technical protection or inherent in the platform used (or the absence of such constraint).

name: RegulationCommunityLevelCode
definition: A code that indicates that a trade item is in compliance with specific applicable government regulations.

name: PackagingRecyclabilityAssessmentInformation
definition: This class includes attributes to provide the recyclability assessment of an item's packaging on the packaging level.

name: CleaningDisinfectingInformation
definition: A group of attributes to help the buyer understand the cleaning and/or disinfecting of a product.

name: DangerousGoodsRegulationCode
definition: Code specifying a dangerous goods regulation. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List DangerousGoodsRegulationCode.

name: DataCarrierTypeCode
definition: Code specifying a data carrier type. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List DataCarrierTypeCode.

name: MeasurementUnitCode_GDSN
definition: Code specifying a unit of measure. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List MeasurementUnitCode.

name: PackageTypeCode_GDSN
definition: The dominant means used to transport, store, handle or display the trade item as defined by the data source.

name: MultiPictureDisplayCapabilityTypeCode
definition: The type of ability to simultaneously display multiple viewing windows on the same screen expressed as a code for example PICTURE_AND_TEXT.

name: CompoundStringAttributeValuePair
definition: A data type that allows for temporary attributes along with associated qualifiers (e.g. unit of measure, currency code) introduced between minor versions.

name: SalesMeasurementTypeCode
definition: Code specifying a sales measurement type code. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List SalesMeasurementTypeCode.

name: StackingPatternTypeCode
definition: Indicates the supply chain process that the particular product may be stacked in.

name: PaymentTermsEventCode
definition: Code specifying a payment terms event. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List PaymentTermsEventCode.

name: SustainabilityProgramInformation
definition: Provides the information on sustainability programs, i.e. programs which are designed to encourage people to buy products with a low(er) environmental footprint.

name: RawMaterialInformation
definition: A set of attributes describing the raw material(s) information of a particular product material.

name: PackagingClaims
definition: Details on a claim for the packaging. In some markets permitted by regulations.

name: TobaccoCannabisInformation
definition: A group of information pertaining to tobacco products, cannabis products, or other products and accessories for smoking. This includes products that contain tobacco, products derived from the cannabis plant, and other smoking accessories designed to enhance the smoking experience.

name: CannabisInformation
definition: A group of attributes providing information on cannabis products and properties.

name: CannabinoidContentInformation
definition: Details specific to Cannabinoid content concerning compounds found in the cannabis products.

name: CannabisPlantInformation
definition: Details specific to cannabis plant type.

name: TerpeneInformation
definition: Detailed information about terpene(s), an aromatic compound found in some plants and products.

name: RawMaterialCode
definition: The code describing the type of raw or recycled material the product material is made from.

name: CannabinoidContentCode
definition: The code identifying how cannabinoid content (chemicals that produce psychoactive effects) is measured relative to the form of the product.

name: CannabinoidTypeCode
definition: The code identifying the type of cannabinoid compounds (chemicals that produce psychoactive effects) found in the cannabis product.

name: CannabisCBDTypeCode
definition: The code that describes the type of Cannabidiol (CBD) in a product, which is one of many active compounds found in the Cannabis plant.

name: TerpeneTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the type of terpene(s) (a compound that gives a product a distinctive smell or taste, especially cannabis) contained in the product.

name: CarrierSubstanceTypeCode
definition: The code specifying the underlying substance (e.g., oils) that is used to absorb compounds to make them more bioavailable (i.e., easily absorbed by the body).

name: ExtractionProcessCode
definition: The code indicating the process to remove oil or resin from plant material to make a concentrate product.

name: FloweringTriggerCode
definition: The code indicating the environmental factors that cause a plant to start to flower (also known as the flowering trigger point).

name: FlowerTrimmingMethodCode
definition: The code indicating the method used for flower trimming and removing plant foliage during harvest.

name: GrowingLightConditionTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the light conditions where plants are grown.

name: TradeItemGenderTypeCode
definition: The code that indicates the gender of the animal, plant or seed that is being sold.

name: SmokingAccessories
definition: A group of attributes providing information on accessories and devices for smoking / inhaling vapor containing nicotine, cannabis or other chemicals.

name: MedicalDeviceSoftwareCode
definition: <sup>The code that identifies if the medical device is itself software, or if the device contains software. </sup>

name: CartridgeDeviceCompatibilityCode
definition: The code indicating the compatibility of the cartridge to the battery or vape pen device.

name: VapeDeviceTypeCode
definition: <sup>The code indicating the device type for vape or electronic cigarette products, a device designed for inhaling vapor containing nicotine, cannabis or other chemicals.</sup>

name: VapingKitCompatibilityCode
definition: <sup>The code indicating that the vaping kit is compatible with e-liquids, dry herb or both.</sup>

name: TerpeneSourceCode
definition: The code indicating the source of terpenes used in the products.

name: DryingMethodTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the method used in the drying process of a product.

name: NutritionalScoreProductCategoryCode
definition: The code indicating the product category of the trade item that is used to calculate the nutritional score.

name: PackingProcessMethodCode
definition: The code indicating the process used to place the product in its packaging.

name: ExternalAgriculturalQualityStandardInformation
definition: The set of information that provides an external standard of agricultural products.

name: AnimalCutCode
definition: The code indicating the cut(s), process and/or part of the animal included or excluded that the trade item contains.

name: EndProductIngredientSchedule
definition: Information on the regulated ingredients used by schools or other institutional meal programs.

name: CarbonFootprintDetail
definition: Carbon footprint detail information.

name: AnimalCutCode(Poultry)
definition: The code indicating the cut(s), process and/or part of the animal included or excluded that the trade item contains.

name: CarbonFootprintHeader
definition: Carbon footprint information.
